Igbo leaders in Kano State yesterday condemned the killing of Hajiya Hariri Jibrin and her four children in Anambra State. A statement signed by the Eze Ndi Igbo in Kano, Igwe Boniface Ibekwe (Ezedioranma) and the President-General of Igbo Community Association (ICA), Kano State, Chief Donatus O. Nwugo, described the incident as “sad and barbaric.” “We are shocked by the barbaric and satanic killing by these unknown gunmen. The criminality is totally unacceptable and reprehensible to Ndigbo of Kano State and all peace-loving people of Nigeria.   Masari begins construction of flyover interchange     Lawmaker marches barefooted for Kaduna-Abuja train victims     World Milk Day: Abuja’s daily production hits 1,500…   “We condemn in strongest term this gruesome murder. “The Ndigbo of Kano State commiserates with the families of all those that have suffered loss of their beloved ones arising from these senseless killings, particularly with the family of the late Hajia Hariri Jibril. May God console and comfort them,” Eze Ibekwe said. The Kano Igbo leaders urged the Federal Government and security agencies to take prompt and decisive measures to fish out the killers.